This is roughly how I installed the velPaint program by Mark Wheadon on Github:

 	https://github.com/MarkWheadon/velocity-painting

the project page is here:

	https://toms3d.org/2018/07/28/velocity-painting-3d-prints/

19958  git clone https://github.com/MarkWheadon/velocity-painting.git
...
19961  make
19962  perl Makefile.PL
19963  make
19964  make manifest
19965  make dist
19966  ll
19967  ./velPaint
19968  ./velPaint
19969  clear
19970  history
19971  make install
19972  sudo make install
19973  ll
19974  velPaint
19975  cd ..
19976  velPaint
19977  sudo apt install libimager-perl
19978  velPaint

